-- ‘Spider-Man’ on Track for $60-$65 Million Weekend, Sony Says
-- B y   D a n   H a r t
-- 2012-07-07T15:20:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-07/-spider-man-on-track-for-60-65-million-weekend-sony-says.html
Sony Corp. (6758)  said “The Amazing Spider-
Man” may earn between $60 million and $65 million in its
opening three-day weekend after it had estimated receipts of
$20.7 million yesterday.  The studio boosted its forecast to earn between $135
million and $140 million over the film’s first six days,
according to an e-mailed statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Hart at 
 dahart@bloomberg.net  